<s> You're right as to why this was added; we had to come to grips with the fact that "casting" is fairly expensive in Java and COM, and some wish to use the DOM in performance-critical environments.  </s>
<s> So, we allow full functionality using just the Node interface, but still support the higher-level interfaces for those who prefer a more object-oriented API.  </s>
<s> ECMAScript in particular is rather limited in its name scoping rules, and "simple" names will tend to clash with legacy APIs, so we have used the naming convention of using the interface name in the methods to minimize the chances for name clashes.  </s>
<s> That will be fixed in the next release.  </s>
